BUILD a full-duplex realtime voice experience for the Companion and Curator AI using Sarvam AI.

## What to build

### 1. Backend WebSocket endpoint: routes/voice.py
Create .claude/command-center/backend/routes/voice.py with:
- WebSocket at /api/voice/{role}/{user_id} (role = "companion" or "curator")
- On connect: open Sarvam STT WebSocket (saaras:v3, en-IN, 16kHz PCM)
- Receive audio chunks from browser → forward to Sarvam STT
- On transcript received → call existing chat pipeline:
  - For companion: use _process_chat() from companion.py
  - For curator: use CuratorEngine.chat() from curator_prompts.py
- Send AI response text to Sarvam TTS WebSocket → stream audio chunks back
- Handle barge-in: if new speech_start while TTS playing → cancel TTS, start new STT

### 2. Register voice router in main.py
Add: from routes import voice
Add: app.include_router(voice.router)

### 3. Frontend voice component: js/components/voice-chat.js
Build reusable voice chat component:
- getUserMedia() for mic access (PCM 16kHz via AudioWorklet or ScriptProcessorNode)
- WebSocket connection to /api/voice/{role}/{user_id}
- Send audio chunks as binary frames
- Receive audio chunks → play via AudioContext
- Visual states: idle, listening (pulsing mic), thinking (dots), speaking (waveform)
- Barge-in: user speaks while AI audio playing → stop playback, send new audio
- Mic toggle button with clear visual indicator

### 4. CSS: css/voice-chat.css
- Mic button styles (idle/active/disabled states)
- Pulsing animation for listening state
- Audio waveform visualization for speaking state
- Responsive layout

### 5. Wire into companion-chat.js and tory-workspace.js
- Add mic button to companion chat header
- Add mic button to curator co-pilot drawer
- Import and init VoiceChat component

### Sarvam AI Details
- SARVAM_API_KEY is in .env (sk_lwifrj09_...)
- Python SDK: sarvamai (pip install sarvamai)
- STT: AsyncSarvamAI().speech_to_text_streaming.connect(model="saaras:v3", mode="transcribe", language_code="en-IN")
- TTS: client.text_to_speech.generate(text, model="bulbul:v2", language_code="en-IN", speaker="meera") 
- For streaming TTS, use text_to_speech_streaming.connect() and send text chunks
- VAD signals: speech_start, speech_end for natural turn detection
- Audio format: PCM 16kHz for STT input, configurable for TTS output

### Important
- The companion.py _process_chat() function takes (user_id, message, session_id, context) and returns a dict with response, mode, sources
- The curator CuratorEngine.chat() takes (nx_user_id, message, session_id) 
- Both are synchronous — wrap in asyncio.run_in_executor() for the WebSocket handler
- Make sure to handle the import path issue: sys.path needs .claude/rag/ directory
